). The status of 
<taxonomicName id="C8FDD7DE27A6A9E8EDDD7246BC75F74E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pauciradiatus">Plagioscion pauciradiatus Steindachner</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BF546D05D1CC6BE63D2E7B6FAB40AA4A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Sciaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubella">Sciaena rubella Schomburgk</taxonomicName>
remains doubtful because the types were not located and the original descriptions are insufficient to allocate these species to any known species of 
<taxonomicName id="F8378F904E66DC3D253757F92540631E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sciaenidae" genus="Plagioscion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="41" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Plagioscion</taxonomicName>
(Casatti, 2003).
</paragraph>
